      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:dfb1e06406981639",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 191,
        "char_start": 13,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Welcome to The Long View. Today we're exploring continuous glucose monitors and what they tell you in depth with Dr. Elena Fischer, researcher in metabolic and longevity science.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 6000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 0,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-02",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Dr. Elena Fischer"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:68eb7203a8da086d",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 270,
        "char_start": 211,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Alex Morgan. This is a topic I've spent decades on.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:ea57d1f280060c4e",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 485,
        "char_start": 284,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "This episode is brought to you by Linear. Linear is the issue tracker built for speed — keyboard-first, fast search, and a clean roadmap view your team actually uses. Get started at linear.com/podcast.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:b1823164b13668e8",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 547,
        "char_start": 485,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Why is systems thinking the part that most analyses get wrong?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:4a0c5855c7156750",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 780,
        "char_start": 567,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "The short answer is CGMs are diagnostic tools more than they are training tools. Teams working with WHOOP run into this constantly. The framing matters because it tells you which trade-offs you're actually making.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:d4bc4106240566ea",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 848,
        "char_start": 794,
        "episode_id": "d24c1620-8d16-54dd-b681-2f2e06c0b579",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Is there a counterexample that would change your view?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e02.txt"
      },
